{"questionId":"20887","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large school has students from Year 6 to Year 12.</p>\n<p>A group of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn></math> students in Year 12 were randomly selected and surveyed to find out how&nbsp;many hours per week they each spend doing homework. Their results are represented by&nbsp;the following cumulative frequency graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a6dbe6a979943ec1273dad19153ad622e904e2d3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the median number of hours per week these Year 12 students spend&nbsp;doing homework.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>evidence of median position&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math>&nbsp;students</p>\n<p>median <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn></math> (hours)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20887","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the median number of hours per week these Year 12 students spend doing homework.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}